Vice President Joe Biden released a statement announcing the passing of his mother, Catherine Eugenia "Jean" Finnegan Biden. She passed away peacefully at their home in Wilmington, Delaware, surrounded by her children, grandchildren, and loved ones. She was 92 years old. Joe Biden described his mother as the center of their family and emphasized the values she instilled in them, such as treasuring family, loyalty, and faith. He also mentioned that her strength will live on in all of them. The statement includes details about Mrs. Biden's background, her marriage to Joseph Robinette Biden, her surviving family members, and information about future services. In lieu of flowers, the family requested that contributions be made to a hospice, the Ministry of Caring in Wilmington, Delaware, or the Naomi Christina Biden Minority Scholarship Fund at Archmere Academy in Claymont, Delaware.